original_recipe:
Prep Time: 23 mins
Cook Time: 20 mins
Total Time: 43 mins
Servings: 6

Ingredients
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 medium onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 pound turkey, cut into bite-sized pieces
2 cups chopped broccoli
2 cups chopped spinach
1 1/2 cups uncooked white rice
1 (14-ounce) can diced tomatoes
2 teaspoons Italian seasoning
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon black pepper
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese

Directions
1. In a wide Dutch oven, warm 1 tablespoon of the olive oil over medium heat. Stir in the onion and cook until it begins to soften and turn glossy, about 5 minutes.
2. Sprinkle the garlic into the pan and cook briefly, stirring, until aromatic, about 1 minute.
3. Add the turkey to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned on the outside and mostly cooked through, 6 to 8 minutes.
4. Add the broccoli and spinach. Cook, tossing everything together, until the vegetables take on a bit of color and soften slightly, 3 to 5 minutes.
5. Stir the rice into the pan along with the broth or tomatoes. Mix everything together and bring just to a simmer.
6. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover, and cook until the grains or starch are tender and the liquid has mostly reduced, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.
7. Stir in any cream and cheese right at the end, letting them melt into the sauce. Taste and add more salt or pepper if you like.
8. Take the pan off the heat. Finish with a handful of fresh herbs and serve right away.

Prep Time: 23 mins
Cook Time: 21 mins
Total Time: 44 mins
Servings: 4

Ingredients
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 medium onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 pound salmon, cut into bite-sized pieces
2 cups chopped cherry tomatoes
2 cups chopped snap peas
8 small flour tortillas or 4 burger buns
2 teaspoons ground cumin
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon black pepper

Directions
1. Heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil in a large heavy-bottomed skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and translucent, 4 to 5 minutes.
2. Add the garlic and cook, stirring constantly, for about 30 seconds, until it is fragrant.
3. Add the salmon to the pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned on the outside and mostly cooked through, 6 to 8 minutes.
4. Fold the cherry tomatoes and snap peas into the pan and cook until they brighten in color and just start to tenderize, about 4 minutes.
5. Pour in the tortillas or buns and any remaining liquids from the ingredient list. Stir well and let the mixture come to a light simmer.
6. Lower the heat and cover the pan. Simmer gently, stirring occasionally, until the base is tender and most of the liquid has been absorbed, about 15 to 20 minutes.
7. Stir in any cream and cheese right at the end, letting them melt into the sauce. Taste and add more salt or pepper if you like.
8. Take the pan off the heat. Finish with a handful of fresh herbs and serve right away.

Prep Time: 16 mins
Cook Time: 21 mins
Total Time: 37 mins
Servings: 6

Ingredients
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 medium onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
2 cups cooked lentils
2 cups chopped mushrooms
2 cups chopped zucchini
4 cups low-sodium chicken broth
2 teaspoons Italian seasoning
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon black pepper
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese
1 cup heavy cream

Directions
1. Set a large deep skillet over medium heat and drizzle in 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add the onion and sautÃ©, stirring from time to time, until it softens and smells sweet, 4 to 6 minutes.
2. Sprinkle the garlic into the pan and cook briefly, stirring, until aromatic, about 1 minute.
3. Increase the heat slightly and add the lentil. Cook, stirring now and then, until the pieces are opaque and beginning to brown, about 7 minutes.
4. Stir in the mushrooms and zucchini and cook for another 3 to 4 minutes, until the vegetables begin to soften around the edges.
5. Pour in the broth and any remaining liquids from the ingredient list. Stir well and let the mixture come to a light simmer.
6. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover, and cook until the grains or starch are tender and the liquid has mostly reduced, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.
7. If using cream or cheese, stir it in during the last few minutes of cooking until melted and the sauce is thickened. Taste and adjust the seasoning with additional salt and pepper as needed.
8. Remove from the heat, sprinkle with chopped fresh herbs, and serve hot.

Prep Time: 19 mins
Cook Time: 22 mins
Total Time: 41 mins
Servings: 4

Ingredients
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 medium onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
2 cups cooked chickpeas, drained and rinsed
2 cups chopped broccoli
2 cups chopped zucchini
1 1/2 cups cooked quinoa or farro
2 teaspoons turmeric
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon black pepper
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese
1 cup heavy cream

Directions
1. In a wide Dutch oven, warm 1 tablespoon of the olive oil over medium heat. Stir in the onion and cook until it begins to soften and turn glossy, about 5 minutes.
2. Add the garlic and cook, stirring constantly, for about 30 seconds, until it is fragrant.
3. Scatter the chickpea pieces into the pan in an even layer. Let them sear for a minute, then stir and continue cooking until no longer pink, 6 to 8 minutes.
4. Add the broccoli and zucchini. Cook, tossing everything together, until the vegetables take on a bit of color and soften slightly, 3 to 5 minutes.
5. Pour in the grains and any remaining liquids from the ingredient list. Stir well and let the mixture come to a light simmer.
6. Turn the heat down to low. Cover and cook, lifting the lid once or twice to stir, until the mixture thickens and the grains soften, 15 to 20 minutes.
7. Near the end of cooking, stir through any dairy ingredients so they melt smoothly. Check the seasoning and adjust with salt and pepper to your preference.
8. Remove from the heat, sprinkle with chopped fresh herbs, and serve hot.

Prep Time: 24 mins
Cook Time: 35 mins
Total Time: 59 mins
Servings: 4

Ingredients
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 medium onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
12 ounces sliced mushrooms
2 cups chopped bell peppers
2 cups chopped kale
4 cups low-sodium chicken broth
2 teaspoons herbes de Provence
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon black pepper
3 tablespoons soy sauce

Directions
1. Set a large deep skillet over medium heat and drizzle in 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add the onion and sautÃ©, stirring from time to time, until it softens and smells sweet, 4 to 6 minutes.
2. Stir in the garlic and cook for 1 minute, just until fragrant, being careful not to let it brown.
3. Scatter the mushroom pieces into the pan in an even layer. Let them sear for a minute, then stir and continue cooking until no longer pink, 6 to 8 minutes.
4. Fold the bell peppers and kale into the pan and cook until they brighten in color and just start to tenderize, about 4 minutes.
5. Stir the broth into the pan along with the broth or tomatoes. Mix everything together and bring just to a simmer.
6. Turn the heat down to low. Cover and cook, lifting the lid once or twice to stir, until the mixture thickens and the grains soften, 15 to 20 minutes.
7. Near the end of cooking, stir through any dairy ingredients so they melt smoothly. Check the seasoning and adjust with salt and pepper to your preference.
8. Remove from the heat and garnish with herbs before serving in warm bowls or plates.
